TY  - JOUR
AU  - Bond, Philip
AU  - Zhong, Hongda
T1  - Buying High and Selling Low: Stock Repurchases and Persistent Asymmetric Information
PY  - 2016
Y1  - 2016/06/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhw005
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 29
IS  - 6
SP  - 1409
EP  - 1452
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - Share prices generally fall when a firm announces a seasoned equity offering (SEO). A standard explanation is that an SEO communicates negative information to investors. We show that if repeated capital market transactions are possible, this same asymmetry of information between firms and investors implies that some firms also repurchase shares in equilibrium. A subset of these firms directly profit from repurchases, while other firms repurchase in order to improve the terms of a subsequent SEO. The possibility of repurchases reduces both SEOs and investment. Overall, our analysis highlights the importance of analyzing SEOs and repurchases in a unified framework.Received June 28, 2014; accepted September 14, 2015 by Editor David Hirshleifer.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhw005
ER  - 



