TY  - JOUR
AU  - Crane, Alan D.
AU  - Michenaud, Sébastien
AU  - Weston, James P.
T1  - The Effect of Institutional Ownership on Payout Policy: Evidence from Index Thresholds
PY  - 2016
Y1  - 2016/06/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhw012
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 29
IS  - 6
SP  - 1377
EP  - 1408
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We show that higher institutional ownership causes firms to pay more dividends. Our identification relies on a discontinuity in ownership around Russell index thresholds. Our estimates indicate that a one-percentage-point increase in institutional ownership causes a $7 million (8%) increase in dividends. We also find differences in shareholder proposals and voting patterns that suggest that even nonactivist institutions play an important role in monitoring firm behavior. The effect of institutional ownership on dividends is stronger for firms with higher expected agency costs.Received December 5, 2014; accepted December 24, 2015 by Editor David Denis.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhw012
ER  - 



